docs.summary: Manage domains that are registered through Wix.

permissions.name: Manage Domains
permissions.description: Request permission to read, create and modify the account's connected domains.

params.name: registeredDomain
params.doc: Information about the domain to register including contact details.

docs.summary:
Creates a `registeredDomain` object and starts the domain registration process
that may take up to 48 hours to resolve.


You must pass the relevant Wix account ID in the header of the call. You may
also pass a Wix site ID in the header of the call. This assigns the domain to 
the site when the registration succeeds. If you don't provide a site ID, the domain
is registered but not assigned to a Wix site. Information about the site is
returned in the `siteInfo` object, while information about the account isn't
returned.

To register a domain and assign it to a site, the site must have an active
[Premium plan](https://support.wix.com/en/article/upgrading-your-site-to-premium-3066683).
However, if you just want to register a domain without connecting it to a
site, the account doesn't need an active Premium plan. In both situations,
the account must own a product that supports linking a domain with the chosen
TLD. Use [Create Package](https://dev.wix.com/api/rest/account-level-apis/resellers/packages/create-package-v2) 
of the Resellers API to add the relevant Premium plan or product to your
customer's site. Contact the [Wix B2B sales team](mailto:bizdev@wix.com)
for details about the available product IDs. 

You can only register a root domain. You can't register a subdomain.

If you try to register a domain that isn't available for purchase or there 
is already a `registeredDomain` object for the specified domain, the call
fails without creating a `registeredDomain` object or starting the
registration process.

Wix tries to register the domain several times, 
but stops in case the process fails too often. Contact the 
[Wix B2B team](mailto:bizdev@wix.com) 
for more information about the number of attempts and their timing.

Wix only checks formal requirements of each field in the `contacts` object, such as 
the maximum number of characters. Wix doesn't check whether the actual domain registrar has 
additional requirements, for example that the postal code is valid in the 
specified country. If there is such a mismatch between the request and the 
registrar's requirements, the call succeeds but the registration process
can't succeed. Read more about 
[contact validations](https://dev.wix.com/api/rest/account-level-apis/registered-domains/contact-validations).

> __Important:__ This call requires an account level API key and cannot be authenticated with the standard authorization header.

docs.summary:
Retrieves a list of up to 100 registered domains.


You must pass the relevant Wix account ID in the header of the call. 

The retrieved domains are sorted by `createdDate` in descending order.

> __Important:__ This call requires an account level API key and cannot be authenticated with the standard authorization header.

members.name: id
members.doc: Domain ID. Identical to `domain`.

members.name: domain
members.doc:
Name of the domain including the
[TLD](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Top-level_domain).
Subdomains aren't supported, you can only register a root domain.
Domain name and TLD must be separated by a dot. For example,
`my-new-domain.com`. Only alphanumeric characters, hyphens, and dots are
supported.

Min: 3 characters  
Max: 63 characters

members.name: productInstanceId
members.doc:
ID of the product instance from the
[Resellers API](https://dev.wix.com/docs/rest/api-reference/account-level-apis/resellers/packages-and-product-instances/packages-object)
that belongs to the `registeredDomain` object.  
Your account must own a product that supports the chosen TLD, regardless of
whether you want to assign the domain to a site or keep it floating. In
case you want to assign the domain to a site, the relevant site must also
own a Premium plan. Contact the [Wix B2B team](mailto:bizdev@wix.com)
for more information about how to become a reseller and a list of available
product IDs.

members.name: createdDate
members.doc:
Date and time the `registeredDomain` object was created in
`YYYY-MM-DDThh:mm:ss.sssZ` format.

members.name: updatedDate
members.doc:
Date and time the `registeredDomain` object was last updated in
`YYYY-MM-DDThh:mm:ss.sssZ` format.

members.name: revision
members.doc:
Revision number, which increments by 1 each time the registered domain
is updated. To prevent conflicting changes, the current revision must be
passed when updating the registered domain.

Ignored when creating a registered domain.

members.name: siteInfo
members.doc:
Information about the Wix site the domain is connected to and whether the
domain is assigned as the primary domain or a redirect.

members.name: contacts
members.doc:
Contact details for the registrant, admin, and tech support of the registered domain.
You can read more about which
[Contact Field Validations](https://https://dev.wix.com/api/rest/account-level-apis/registered-domains/contact-field-validations)
are implemented.

members.name: status
members.doc:
Status of the registered domain.

+ `"UNKNOWN_STATUS"`: There's no information about the status of the registered domain.
+ `"PENDING_REGISTRATION"`: Wix has started the domain registration process, but the domain hasn't been successfully registered yet.
+ `"ACTIVE"`: The domain has been registered successfully and is active.
+ `"FAILED_REGISTRATION"`: Wix has tried to register the domain, but has stopped the process due to too many failed attempts. Contact the [Wix B2B team](mailto:bizdev@wix.com) for more information.
+ `"CANCELED"`: The domain has been canceled and isn't active any longer.

members.name: statusInfo
members.doc: option (.wix.api.aligned_with_enum).field = "status";

members.name: icannConfirmationStatus
members.doc:
ICANN confirmation status.

+ `"UNKNOWN_ICANN_CONFIRMATION_STATUS"`: There's no information about the status of the ICANN confirmation process.
+ `"PENDING"`: Wix has started the ICANN confirmation process, but not all contacts have confirmed the domain yet.
+ `"CONFIRMED_BY_ALL"`: The domain has been successfully confirmed by all contacts.
+ `"EXPIRED"`: The domain hasn't been confirmed by all contacts before the ICANN confirmation process has expired. The domain isn't active and a new confirmation process must be started. Contact the [Wix B2B team](mailto:bizdev@wix.com) for more information.

members.name: icannConfirmationStatusInfo
members.doc: Details about the ICANN confirmation status.

members.name: dnsPropagationStatus
members.doc:
DNS propagation status.

+ `"UNKNOWN_DNS_PROPAGATION_STATUS"`: There's no information about the domain's DNS propagation status.
+ `"IN_PROGRESS"`: The domain's DNS propagation process has started but hasn't successfully completed yet.
+ `"COMPLETED"`: The domain's DNS propagation process has successfully finished.
+ `"FAILED"`: The domain's DNS propagation process has failed.

members.name: expirationDate
members.doc:
Expiration date of the registered domain in `YYYY-MM-DDThh:mm:ss.sssZ`
format. The domain registration must be actively extended before the
expiration date.

members.name: pendingRegistrationInfo
members.doc:
Information about a domain that hasn't been successfully registered
yet. Includes the timestamp of the latest registration attempt.

members.name: failedRegistrationInfo
members.doc:
Information about a domain that couldn't be registered. Includes
failure code and message.

members.name: registrant
members.doc: Contact information for the domain registrant.

members.name: admin
members.doc: Contact information for the domain admin.

members.name: tech
members.doc: Contact information for the tech support of the domain.

members.name: firstName
members.doc:
First name. Only
[alphanumerical characters](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Alphanumericals)
are supported.

Min: 2 characters  
Max: 64 characters

members.name: lastName
members.doc:
Last name. Only
[alphanumerical characters](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Alphanumericals)
are supported.

Min: 2 characters  
Max: 64 characters

members.name: email
members.doc:
Email address.  Only
[alphanumerical characters](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Alphanumericals)
and a single `@` are supported. Wix doesn't validate that the email address
exists.

Min: 3 characters  
Max: 64 characters before the `@` and 63 after

members.name: address
members.doc:
Address details, including street name and house number. Only
[alphanumerical characters](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Alphanumericals)
are supported.

Min: 2 characters  
Max: 64 characters

members.name: city
members.doc:
City. Only
[alphanumerical characters](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Alphanumericals)
are supported.

Min: 2 characters  
Max: 64 characters

members.name: subdivisionCode
members.doc:
Subdivision code in
[ISO-3166 alpha-2](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/ISO_3166-1_alpha-2#Officially_assigned_code_elements)
format. Only
[alphanumerical characters](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Alphanumericals)
are supported.  
__Required__ for these countries:
`”AE"`, `"AR"`, `"AT"`, `"AU"`, `"BE"`, `"BR"`, `"CA"`, `"CH"`, `"CL"`,
`"CO"`, `"CR"`, `"CZ"`, `"DE"`, `"DK"`, `"ES"`, `"FI"`, `"FR"`, `"GR"`,
`"IE"`, `"IN"`, `"IT"`, `"JP"`, `"KR"`, `"MX"`, `"MY"`, `"NL"`, `"NO"`,
`"NZ"`, `"PE"`, `"PL"`, `"PT"`, `"RU"`, `"SE"`, `"SG"`, `"TH"`, `"TR"`,
`"TW"`, `"UA"`, `"US"`, `”ZA”`.

Min: 2 characters  
Max: 2 characters

members.name: postalCode
members.doc:
Postal code. Only
[alphanumerical characters](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Alphanumericals)
are supported.

Min: 2 characters  
Max: 16 characters

members.name: countryCode
members.doc:
Country code in
[ISO-3166 alpha-1](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/ISO_3166-2#Subdivisions_included_in_ISO_3166-1)
format. Only
[alphanumerical characters](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Alphanumericals)
are supported. Wix doesn't validate that the postal code is valid for the
given country.

Min: 2 characters  
Max: 2 characters

members.name: phone
members.doc:
Phone number. Only
[alphanumerical characters](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Alphanumericals)
are supported. For example, `+15551234567`. Wix doesn't validate that the
phone number belongs to the specified country.

Min: 2 characters  
Max: 20 characters

members.name: company
members.doc:
Company name. Only
[alphanumerical characters](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Alphanumericals)
are supported.

Max: 2 characters  
Max: 64 characters

members.name: pending
members.doc: Details about domains with `"PENDING"` ICANN confirmation status.

members.name: expired
members.doc: Details about domains with `"EXPIRED"` ICANN confirmation status.

members.name: expirationDate
members.doc:
Expiration date of the ICANN confirmation process in
`YYYY-MM-DDThh:mm:ss.sssZ` format. All contacts must confirm the domain
before this date or the domain won't be active.

members.name: notConfirmedBy
members.doc:
Email addresses of the contacts who haven't confirmed the domain with ICANN
yet.

members.name: notConfirmedBy
members.doc:
Email addresses of the contacts who haven't confirmed the domain with ICANN
in time.

members.name: id
members.doc: ID of the site to which the domain is assigned.

members.name: assignmentType
members.doc:
Whether the domain is assigned as the primary domain or a redirect.
Read more about [primary and redirected domains](https://support.wix.com/en/article/switching-your-primary-and-redirected-domains).
__Note:__ When you connect a domain or subdomain, you can't pass `"UNKNOWN_ASSIGNMENT_TYPE"`
in the request of the Create Registered Domain call.

+ `"UNKNOWN_ASSIGNMENT_TYPE"`: There's no information about the assignment type.
+ `"PRIMARY"`: The domain is assigned as the primary domain to the Wix site.
+ `"REDIRECT"`: The domain is assigned as a redirect to the Wix site.

members.name: assignmentInfo
members.doc: Extra information about the assignment

members.name: redirectInfo
members.doc: Extra details in case assignment type is redirect.

members.name: latestAttempt
members.doc:
Information about the latest attempt to register
the domain. Wix tries to register the domain several times, in case the
first attempt is unsuccessful. You can contact the
[Wix B2B team](mailto:bizdev@wix.com)
for more information about the number of attempts and their timing.

members.name: code
members.doc:
Failure code.

+ `"UNKNOWN_FAILURE_CODE"`: There's no information about the failure code.
+ `"OTHER"`: There was a failure, but none of the listed failure codes applies.

members.name: message
members.doc: Failure message.

members.name: number
members.doc: Number of the latest attempt to register the domain.

members.name: timestamp
members.doc:
Date and time of the latest domain registration attempt in
`YYYY-MM-DDThh:mm:ss.sssZ` format.

members.name: primaryDomain
members.doc: Primary domain the redirect points to.

members.name: limit
members.doc:
Number of domains to load.

Min: `0`
Max: `100`

members.name: cursor
members.doc:
Pointer to the next or previous page in the list of results.

You can get the relevant cursor token
from the `pagingMetadata` object in the previous call's response.
Not relevant for the first request.

members.name: count
members.doc: Number of domains returned in the response.

members.name: cursors
members.doc: Offset that was requested.

members.name: hasNext
members.doc:
Indicates if there are more results after the current page.
 If `true`, another page of results can be retrieved.
 If `false`, this is the last page.

members.name: next
members.doc: Cursor pointing to next page in the list of results.

members.name: prev
members.doc: Cursor pointing to previous page in the list of results.

members.name: registeredDomain
members.doc: Information about the domain to register including contact details.

members.name: registeredDomain
members.doc: Created registered domain.

members.name: registeredDomainId
members.doc: ID of the registered domain to retrieve.

members.name: registeredDomain
members.doc: Retrieved registered domain.

members.name: paging
members.doc: Cursor paging options.

members.name: pagingMetadata
members.doc: Metadata about the returned list of registered domains.

members.name: registeredDomains
members.doc: Retrieved registered domains.

docs.summary:
Possible values are:
  • UNKNOWN_STATUS
  • PENDING_REGISTRATION
  • ACTIVE
  • FAILED_REGISTRATION
  • CANCELED

Possible values are:
  • UNKNOWN_ASSIGNMENT_TYPE
  • PRIMARY
  • REDIRECT

the confirmation status types, a record: starts at pending ends either at confirmed_by_all or expired Possible values are:
  • UNKNOWN_ICANN_CONFIRMATION_STATUS
  • PENDING
  • CONFIRMED_BY_ALL
  • EXPIRED

Possible values are:
  • UNKNOWN_DNS_PROPAGATION_STATUS
  • COMPLETED
  • FAILED
  • IN_PROGRESS
